# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ABERP .gitignore
# Notes:
#   - Cargo.lock IS committed (ADR-0007: pinned dependency versions,
#     reproducible builds, --locked CI builds). Do not add it here.
#   - Tenant data files, secrets, and audit mirrors must never be
#     committed. They are listed below explicitly.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Rust ---------------------------------------------------
/target
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# --- Python (S269 aberp-cad-extract) ------------------------
# The CAD extractor crate ships in `python/aberp-cad-extract/`.
# Build artefacts, venvs, and pytest caches stay local.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.venv/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# --- Node / Svelte / Tauri frontend -------------------------
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.svelte-kit/
.vite/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Tauri build output
src-tauri/target/
src-tauri/gen/
# Custom Tauri layout: aberp-ui places its Tauri crate at the workspace
# member root (apps/aberp-ui/) rather than the conventional src-tauri/
# subdir, so tauri-build emits `apps/aberp-ui/gen/` instead of
# `src-tauri/gen/`. The schemas there are codegen output from
# capabilities/*.json + tauri.conf.json and regenerate on every
# `cargo build` — checking them in adds noise to every capability tweak.
apps/aberp-ui/gen/

# --- ABERP runtime data (NEVER commit) ----------------------
# Per-tenant DuckDB files and their audit-ledger mirrors.
*.duckdb
*.duckdb.wal
*.duckdb-wal
*.audit.log
/data/
/tenants/
/var/

# --- Secrets (NEVER commit) ---------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
.secrets/
secrets/

# Vendored CA trust anchors are PUBLIC certificates that ARE the
# pin per ADR-0020 §1 ("NAV server-certificate issuing root is
# pinned in ABERP's trust store"). They must be committed; the
# blanket *.pem rule above would otherwise hide them. Scope kept
# narrow — only files under crates/*/roots/ are un-ignored, so a
# stray *.pem anywhere else still trips the secret guard.
!crates/*/roots/*.pem

# --- OS noise -----------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
*~
.directory

# --- Editor / IDE -------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.shared.json
.zed/
*.swp
*.swo
*.code-workspace

# --- Logs (local dev) ---------------------------------------
*.log
logs/

# --- Test / coverage ----------------------------------------
coverage/
.nyc_output/
.lcov

# --- Misc ---------------------------------------------------
.cache/
.tmp/
tmp/
*.bak
*.orig
CLAUDE.md

# --- Between-session handoffs (local-only) ------------------
# Notes from one design/build session to the next. Not part of
# the repo's design or code history; not for collaborators.
/_handoffs/

# --- Claude Code session runtime (local-only) ---------------
# Per-session scheduler lock (sessionId + pid); runtime junk, never
# part of the repo's history.
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# --- S279 / PR-265 — pricing-pipeline artifacts -------------
# Downloaded customer CADs + rendered indicative PDFs land under
# this dir (configurable via ABERP_QUOTE_PIPELINE_ARTIFACT_DIR).
# Per-tenant local cache, never part of the repo's history.
quote-artifacts/

# Local-only working doc — keep out of the repo (per owner decision)
docs/EIC_DUALUSE_BRIEFING_HANDOFF.md
